        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 1:41AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 141 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 14
miles northwest of Idabel, or 29 miles east of Hugo, moving northeast
at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Millerton, Wright City, Slim, Glover, and Golden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
